Conclusion: The model is clinically viable for screening P. falciparum, satisfying the primary hackathon objective.

ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture Design (The "Agentic" Approach)

MicroSmart PF follows a Neuro-Symbolic architecture, separating perception from reasoning.

Component A: Vision Agent (The Eye)

Tech: Ultralytics YOLOv8

Input: Raw Microscopy Images (Giemsa stain).

Output: Structured JSON (Cell Counts, Parasite Stages).

Component B: Reasoning Agent (The Brain)

Tech: Cerebras Inference API (Llama 3.3 - 70B)

Input: JSON Data + WHO Guidelines (System Prompt).

Output: Natural Language Medical Report, Severity Assessment, Treatment Recommendations.

Component C: Memory (The Nervous System)

Tech: LiquidMetal Raindrop

Function: Stores patient history and image embeddings for longitudinal analysis.